      "content": "The \"living constitution\" approach is a thinly veiled attempt by liberal justices to impose their own policy preferences on the text, rather than faithfully interpreting the Constitution as written. Originalism, on the other hand, is a legitimate approach that seeks to understand the original meaning of the Constitution, but it can be selectively applied to fit a specific ideological agenda. The conservative justices' originalist approach is more nuanced and grounded in historical context, whereas liberal justices' \"living constitution\" approach is often a euphemism for judicial activism.",
